## Database Design

### PostgreSQL (Prisma) — `Users` and relational data

| Model | Key Fields |
|---|---|
| `Users` | `users_id`, `user_name`, `email`, `phone_number`, `gender`, `image`, `dept`, `batch`, `student_id` |
| `LostItem` | `item_id`, `name`, `description`, [date](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/dp%20project%20work/CampusConnect/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js#114-163), `location`, `image`, `ownerId` → Users |
| `BloodRequest` | `request_id`, `blood_group`, `location`, `deadline`, `requesterId` → Users |
| `DonorRecord` | `donor_id`, `blood_group`, `location`, `last_donated`, `userId` → Users (1:1) |
| `RoommateListing` | `id`, `area`, `rent`, `facilities`, `isGirlsOnly`, `studentsInfo` (JSON), `postedBy` → Users |

### MongoDB (Mongoose) — Feature data

| Model | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Society` | Society profiles with `panelMembers[]`, `pastGallery[]`, `admins[]`, `adminRequests[]`, `followers[]` |
| `Event` | Society events with `societyId`, `registrations[]`, categories: Workshop/Competition/Seminar/Other |
| `Feedback` | Anonymous feedback with categories (17 campus areas), `comments[]`, `likes[]` |
| `MarketplacePost` | Listings with `preOrders[]`, `sizeSpecifications[]`, seller info, `productStatus` |
| [Notification](file:///c:/Users/User/Desktop/dp%20project%20work/CampusConnect/Backend/controllers/notification.controller.js#4-50) | Cross-module notifications with `recipientId` (userId or `"all"` for broadcast) |
| `NotificationRead` | Per-user read receipts for broadcast notifications (separate from `isRead` on Notification) |

