## Authentication Flow

```
1. User clicks "Sign in with Google" on Login page
2. Firebase SDK handles OAuth → returns idToken
3. Frontend POSTs idToken to POST /api/auth/google-signin
4. Backend verifies idToken with Firebase Admin SDK
5. Backend upserts user in PostgreSQL (Prisma)
6. Backend signs a JWT (secret: 'Blink') with user email → returned to frontend
7. Frontend saves JWT to sessionStorage ("authToken") + user object to sessionStorage ("user")
8. All subsequent API calls send: Authorization: Bearer <JWT>
9. VerifyToken.js middleware decodes JWT, looks up user in Postgres, attaches user to req.verifiedUser
```

> [!WARNING]
> The JWT secret is a hardcoded string `'Blink'`. This is a security risk in production. It should be moved to an environment variable.

